Key Match Events: Jackson Chourio delivered a single in the fifth inning that scored the first run and opened the door to a five-run inning.
William Contreras hit a two-run home run to cap a rally that made a winner of Freddy Peralta.
Pre-Game Insights: The article does not contain any pre-game insights.
Post-Match Reflections: Peralta stated, 'I told you guys before, I knew at some point I was going to feel good and everything was going to work again.'
Peralta also mentioned, 'I’m working hard. Just keep it that way until the end of the regular season, and then after that, it’s different baseball.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Chourio hit a Statcast-projected 449-foot home run on Tuesday.
A digital marker of Chourio’s clout was added in the form of a baseball with his No. 11 in batting practice on Wednesday.
Contreras hit a Statcast-projected 435-foot two-run home run to cap a rally.
Others: The youngest player in Major League Baseball continues to develop.
Chourio’s.886 OPS ranked 17th of 133 qualifying hitters in MLB.
His 6.09 plate appearances per strikeout was 32nd-best.
Peralta has held opponents to one earned run on nine hits over 17 innings in his past three starts.
